Add a Power Automate flow to update the forecast data automatically.

The flow must:
1. Run daily at 8:00 AM
2. Query coepp_pronostico ordered by Pronostico_Fecha_Dttm descending
3. Filter only where Pronostico_Etiqueta_Desc = "Pronostico Oficial"
4. Take the most recent record and compare with current Active forecast
5. If a newer forecast exists:
   a. Insert new header record in coepp_pronostico 
      (Pronostico_Estado = Active)
   b. Insert all detail records in coepp_pronostico_detalles
   c. SYNC Child PAD Master (coepp_maestro_pad_hijos):
      - PAD present in new forecast → set Active
      - PAD NOT present in new forecast → set Inactive
   d. Set all previous forecasts as Inactive
   e. Send email to Assurance group: new forecast available
6. If no newer forecast exists: do nothing, log result

Use only existing tables:
- coepp_pronostico
- coepp_pronostico_detalles
- coepp_maestro_pad_hijos

Add this flow to the Solution Plan as a new artifact.

RESPUESTA
The new scheduled flow has been added to the Solution Plan as an architectural artifact named Daily forecast updater. No data model or business requirement changes were needed, and no app implementation changes apply.

The plan is now consistent and includes the new Power Automate flow.
